<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="710" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-25"><hi rend="italic">April 25,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Sanguily was committed yesterday to court-martial for another charge, and
                            as Aguirre and Carrillo had not yet been transferred to civil court, I
                            have protested in the name of the Government of the United States in the
                            three cases.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>